//Should we use a new class to contain position to a point?

Shape (Interface):
   - getType
   - getName
   - getColor //what should this return? Should it return a String or Color object?
   - getAppears
   - getDisappears
   - getPositionX
   - getPositionY

ShapeImpl (abstract class)
    Constructor:
        -

    Methods:
        - All the methods from the Shape interface, except getType


Rectangle (subclass of ShapeImpl):
    Constructor:
        - super
        - shapeType
        - height
        - width

    Methods:
        - getType
        - getHeight
        - getWidth

Oval (subclass of ShapeImpl):
    Constructor:
        - super
        - shapeType
        - radiusX
        - radiusY

    Methods:
        - getType
        - getRadiusX
        - getRadiusY

--------------------------------------------------

//When we transform the shape, we don't want to change the original shape but create a
//copy

Transformation (Interface):
    - addTransformation
    - removeTransformation

TransformationImpl (subtype):
    Constructor:
        - name
        - Color(r, g, b);
        - positionX
        - positionY
        - width / radiusX
        - height / radiusY
        - appears
        - disappears

Moving (subclass):
    Constructor:
        - super
        - transformType

    Methods:
        - setPositionX
        - setPositionY
        - getTransformType
        - getName
        - getColor
        - getPositionX
        - getPositionY
        - getWidth/getRadiusX
        - getHeight/getRadiusY
        - getAppears
        - getDisappears

Scaling (subclass):
    Constructor:
        - super
        - transformType


    Methods:
        - set Width/RadiusX
        - set Height/RadiusY
        - getTransformType
        - getName
        - getColor
        - getPositionX
        - getPositionY
        - getWidth/getRadiusX
        - getHeight/getRadiusY
        - getAppears
        - getDisappears


changeColor (subclass):
    Constructor:
        - super
        - transformType

    Methods:
        - setColor
        - getTransformType
        - getName
        - getColor
        - getPositionX
        - getPositionY
        - getWidth/getRadiusX
        - getHeight/getRadiusY
